      "voorwaarden": [
        {
          "beschrijving": {
            "en-x-generated": "<h3>Nuisance premium</h3><p>Your company is eligible for the nuisance premium if:</p><ul><li>it employs (at company level, not establishment level) <strong>a maximum of 9 employees</strong>. Temporary workers are not counted.</li><li>the establishment concerned is <strong>seriously inconvenienced </strong>by public works. This means that:<ul><li>the carriageway is fully or partially closed</li><li>the works have a surface area of more than 50<sup>m2</sup> </li><li>the works last at least 30 consecutive calendar days</li></ul></li><li>it carries out activities or provides services that require <strong>personal and direct contact with customers</strong> and are therefore difficult to carry out on site. Specifically, this includes retail trade (shopkeepers), catering and certain services (retail). The NACE code of the enterprise's main activity must appear on <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/media/376\">the list of acceptable NACE codes for the granting of the nuisance premium</a> (only NACE codes 'Group 1'.)</li><li>the establishment concerned has <strong>fixed opening hours</strong> </li><li><p>the establishment <strong>is located within the nuisance zone</strong>. To determine a zone of severe nuisance, the registered data in the GIPOD, the database of road works, are considered. All road sections and intersections that overlap with the GIPOD groundwork zone constitute the nuisance zone. The GIPOD groundwork zone is the zone within which road works are carried out. A road section is the part of the road between two consecutive intersections.</p></li></ul><p><a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/hinderpremie/voorwaarden-om-aanmerking-te-komen-voor-een-hinderpremie\">More information on the exact conditions for the nuisance premium</a> can be found on the VLAIO website.</p><h3>Additional closure premium</h3><p>If you <strong>have to temporarily close your establishment</strong> due to public works, you may be eligible for an additional closure premium. Your enterprise is eligible if:</p><ul><li>it has received the notification letter (even if you did not ultimately apply for the nuisance premium)</li><li>the affected establishment <strong>has to close its doors</strong> for <strong>at least 21 consecutive calendar days</strong> due to serious nuisance caused by public works.</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/hinderpremie/voorwaarden-om-aanmerking-te-komen-voor-een-hinderpremie\">More information on the exact conditions for the closure premium</a> can be found on the VLAIO website.</p><h3>Individual closure premium</h3><p>Entrepreneurs who are <strong>not selected</strong> for the nuisance premium and/or the closure premium may <strong>still</strong> be entitled to a separate closure premium in certain specific cases. Specifically, this concerns <strong>a limited number of liberal professions and services</strong> (general practitioner, specialist, dentist, psychiatrist, physiotherapist, veterinary surgeon, lawyer, notary, photographer...), regardless of whether the establishment concerned is located inside or outside the nuisance zone. The NACE code of the main activity must appear on the <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/media/376\">list of acceptable NACE codes</a> (only NACE codes 'Group 2').</p><p><a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/hinderpremie/aanvraagprocedure/je-ondervindt-ernstige-hinder-door-werken/je\">More information on the individual closure premium</a> can be found on the VLAIO website.</p><h3>Video</h3><p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/ZyRmqSghMpE\">Watch the informative video</a> on the nuisance premium and the closure premium.</p>",
